node.title: Cheerleader Makayla Noble Says It's 'Insane' Freak Accident Hospitalized Her for 8 Weeks
node.description: The teenager suffered a severe spinal cord injury on September 20, which left her paralyzed from the chest down and unable to move her hands.

node.title: U.S. added to list of "backsliding" democracies for 1st time
node.description: The Stockholm-based International IEDA organization says a "visible deterioration" of democratic principles began in the U.S. in 2019.

node.title: A New Search for Jimmy Hoffa
node.description: A deathbed statement by a man who claimed to have buried Hoffa’s body, repeated years later by his son, sent the F.B.I. to Jersey City for a “site survey.”

node.title: NASA Probe, Fastest Object Built by Humans, Passes Sun at Record-Breaking 364,621 mph
node.description: On its 10th flyby of the sun, the Parker Solar Probe hit record speeds that would see it get from New York to London in just over half a minute.

node.title: Entire West Coast Officially Has No Republican Statewide Elected Officials
node.description: Effective Monday, a Democrat will hold the title of Washington Secretary of State—a position that's been held by a Republican for more than 50 years.
